# Local credentials (template)

Copy this file to `CREDENTIALS.local.md` (gitignored) and adjust for your environment.
Do not commit real production passwords.

## Default role passwords (dev / first gateway boot)

| Role | Default password | Gateway env (first boot only) | PWA local dev env |
|------|------------------|--------------------------------|-------------------|
| User | `DevUser!1` | `INITIAL_USER_PASSWORD` | `VITE_DEV_AUTH_USER` |
| Installer | `DevInstall!1` | `INITIAL_INSTALLER_PASSWORD` | `VITE_DEV_AUTH_INSTALLER` |
| Manufacturer | `DevMfg!1` | `INITIAL_MANUFACTURER_PASSWORD` | `VITE_DEV_AUTH_MANUFACTURER` |
| Support override | `DevSupport!1` | `INITIAL_SUPPORT_PASSWORD` | `VITE_DEV_AUTH_SUPPORT` |

Support override is not a role in the UI: it signs in as **User** or **Installer** when that password is used instead of the role password.

## Installer ID (fleet)

There is **no single default installer ID** in the repo.

- On the **login** screen (Installer role), you type **Installer ID** yourself. It is stored on the gateway session and used to filter `GET /api/sites` and to tag new `sites/<siteId>.json` files (`installer_id`).
- **MQTT discovery** payloads may include `installer_id` or `installerId`; that string should **match** the ID you used at login for fleet APIs to return those sites.
- For **local dev** the field is optional; for realistic fleet sync testing, pick a stable value (e.g. `installer-demo`) and use the same value in discovery JSON and at login.

